    <thetext>Description of problem:
When a shutdown is invoked by a script or program systemd-logind segfaults and crashes and the shutdown does not occur.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 229


How reproducible: Always


Steps to Reproduce:
1. systemd-run bash -c &apos;exec -a shutdown systemctl -P&apos;


Actual results:
Shutdown does not occur and systemd-logind segfaults


Expected results:
System shutsdown.


Additional info:
systemd bug about the issue: https://github.com/systemd/systemd/issues/2796
systemd patch to fix the issue: https://github.com/systemd/systemd/commit/b4944d2df248fbd2f96a4b9b4fe02fe0c1af7499

This has been fixed in systemd version 230</thetext>
